The '''Maxwell Award''' is presented annually to the [[college football]] player judged by a panel of [[sportscaster]]s, [[sportswriter]]s, and [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] [[head coach]]es and the membership of the [[Maxwell Football Club]] to be the best all-around in the United States. The [[award]] is named after [[Tiny Maxwell|Robert "Tiny" Maxwell]], a [[Swarthmore College]] football player, coach, and sportswriter. [[Johnny Lattner]] (1952, 1953) and [[Tim Tebow]] (2007, 2008) are the only players to have won the award twice. It is the college equivalent of the [[Bert Bell Award]] of the [[National Football League]], also given out by the Maxwell Club.<ref name=Hornung/><ref name=Blanda/>

